<div class="main_title">
  FUGUE-na Search:
</div>

<div id="fugue_search_form" class="blue_link">
  <% form_for(:fugue_search, @fugue_search, :url => { :action => "create" }) do |f| %>

    <p>
      <%= f.error_messages %>
    </p>

    <p>
    <%= label :fugue_search, :type, "* Search against: " %>
    <%= select_tag "type", options_for_select(%w[DNA RNA], "DNA") %>-binding SCOP families
    [<%= link_to "?", "#search_against_box", :id => "search_against_box_link" %>]
    
    </p>

    <p>
    <%= label :fugue_search, :name, "* Name of your sequence (optional): " %>
    <%= f.text_field :name, :size => 30 %>
    </p>

    <p>
    <%= label :fugue_search, :email, "* Email: " %>
    <%= f.text_field :email, :size => 40 %>
    [<%= link_to "?", "#email_box", :id => "email_box_link" %>]
    </p>

    <p>
    <%= label :fugue_search, :zcutoff, "* Z-value cutoff: " %>
    <%= f.text_field :zcutoff, :size => 5 %>
    [<%= link_to "?", "#zcutoff_box", :id => "zcutoff_box_link" %>]
    </p>

    <p>
    <%= label :fugue_search, :sequence, "* Enter your amino acid sequence: " %><br />
    <%= f.text_area :sequence, :rows => 7, :cols => 60, :class => "fugue_search_text_area" %><br />
    (Please use FASTA or pure amino acid format.)<br />
    </p>

    <p>
      <%= f.submit "Submit" %>
    </p>

  <% end %>
</div>

<h3>References</h3>
<ul>
  <li>
    Shi, J., Blundell, T. L. &amp; Mizuguchi, K. (2001), J Mol Biol, 310(1), 243-57.
  </li>
</ul>

<div id="search_against_box">
  BIPA currently contains 87 FUGUE profiles of DNA-binding SCOP families and 72 profiles of RNA-binding families. The profiles were generated using extended environment-specific substitution tables taking account of atomic interfactions between amino acids and nucleic acids. Preliminary tests have confirmed the profiles based on the extended ESSTs ourperform <%= link_to "conventional ESSTs", "http://www-cryst.bioc.cam.ac.uk/ESST/", :popup => true %> considering only structural restraints such as secondary struture, solvent accessibility, and internal hydrogen bonds and disulphide bonds in terms of remote homology detection for nucleic acid-binding protein families.
</div>

